    • getSuccessfulResponseBody

      @Nullable protected Object getSuccessfulResponseBody​(@Nonnull retrofit2.Response<?> response, @Nonnull Type returnType, @Nonnull Annotation[] annotations, @Nonnull retrofit2.Retrofit retrofit)
      Force calls a typed converter if HTTP status code 204/205 or Response.body() return null This ensures that the request body is processed correctly for the Type. If an exception was thrown and method Response.isSuccessful() returned false, then null will be returned without throwing an exception.
      Parameters:
      response - - Retrofit call response
      returnType - - Successful model Type
      annotations - - list of annotations for the called API method
      retrofit - - HTTP client
      Returns:
      Successful model
      Throws:
      ConvertCallException - ConvertCallException If the body of a successful response is not convertible

      Converting Response.errorBody() to an error model Type. If an exception was thrown and method Response.isSuccessful() returned true, then null will be returned without throwing an exception.
